50|$|Flixbus {{services}} run {{in cooperation}} with regional bus companies from all over Europe. Local partners {{are responsible for the}} day-to-day running of routes, while Flixbus {{is in charge of the}} official authorizations required to operate the long-distance network. Flixbus handles network planning, marketing, pricing, quality management and customer service. This business model is highly scalable and has enabled the company to grow quickly. On the other hand, the quality of buses is subject to the fleet available <b>to</b> <b>subcontractors.</b> Competitors who own all or most of their buses can guarantee consistent service. Flixbus has also often handed off the risk of low occupancy <b>to</b> <b>subcontractors</b> as their bottom line depends on the fare revenue of the routes they operate.|$|R
