25|$|Construction law: In Canada and Minnesota monies owed by {{employers}} to contractors or by contractors <b>to</b> <b>subcontractors</b> on construction projects must by law {{be held in}} trust. In the event of contractor insolvency, this makes it much more likely that subcontractors will be paid for work completed.|$|R
